  "text": "Some results from [P97] now follow from standard properties of the fine potential theory and the fine topology. For example [CITATION_1] Theorem 3.6 (2) ] is the partitioning the set K into the fine connected components of int f K and singleton sets for peak points (i.e. the set ∂ f K) forms an equivalence relation, [CITATION_2] Theorem 3.6 (3) ] is the fine minimum principle, and [P97, Theorem 3.6 (4)] is that fine connected components have positive measure. We can now extend/rephrase some results of [P97] and use them to obtain some new results. Proof. In [P97] Poletsky defines I(x) as the set of points y ∈ K with the property that for any ε > 0 there exists a µ ∈ J x (K) with µ(B(y, ε)) > 0 and in [CITATION_3] Theorem 3.6 (1)] proves that I(x) = Q(x). The result follows from Corollary 3.4.",
